Show HN: Data Painter – A Different Way to Interact with Your Data
text:
Data Painter is RATH's new feature to interact with your data. It helps you to specify complex visual patterns and find explanations and potential causals.

It allows you to do on-flight data labeling, cleaning or even create new features does not exited in original dataset. Everything can be done with a brush tool(painter), You can even play with your data with your fingers on mobile.

RATH is an open-source alternative to Tableau, but with more automations. Feedbacks and suggestions are appreciated.

RATH's Github: https://github.com/Kanaries/Rath

RATH's HomePage: https://kanaries.net/

Show HN: Send private valentines, using homomorphic encryption
text:
Hi HN! I'm a cofounder of Blyss.dev, a YC W23 company building an SDK for homomorphic encryption.

In recent HN discussions of homomorphic encryption, there seems to be a common opinion that it is "too slow to use". I thought it'd be fun to put together a quick, seasonal demo challenging that assumption - here's a realtime database that supports private reads via FHE, used as the backend for an otherwise simple CRUD app. Please do kick the tires!

if my 3am engineering does fall over, and the demo breaks, you can still check out our github repo [0] for more detail on what we think you can practically do with FHE today.

[0] https://github.com/blyssprivacy/sdk

Ask HN: Tools to integrate all customer feedback channels
text:
We're a growing SaaS (hoping to double ARR this year), which means we're no longer in the same room or even the same building or same country.

I'm tasked with being the "voice of the customer." We get customer feedback through a ton of channels:

- Slack conversations - Our community - Surveys - Sales conversations - Hubspot notes - Zoom recorded calls - Customer success 1:1s - Product research calls

Different people are coming with different answers to different questions and we realize this won't scale.

We've tried to create FAQs but nobody looks at them or submits questions.

Many of you must have solved for this problem. Humbly asking for any wisdom you may be willing to share ;-).

Is there a tech-enabled solution to collect all the data and prioritize/have an "answer of record"? Is it a culture/management thing? Both?

Thank you!
